; Variable identifiers are case-insensitive (manual 3.3.2: "No distinction
; is made between uppercase and lowercase characters"): lAYER_HEIGHT,
; LAYER_HEIGHT and layer_height are all the same variable. Seen in a real
; program that declares a typo'd name but assigns the intended one.
DEF REAL lAYER_HEIGHT
LAYER_HEIGHT = 2.5

G1 X0 Y0 Z0 F1000
Z=IC(layer_height)
Z=IC(Layer_Height)
R1 = LAYER_HEIGHT * 4
X = r1
M30
